      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's nice of you to say, but it doesn't change the reality. Every time they come over, I see it in their eyes—the exhaustion. They shouldn't have to spend their weekends cleaning up after me or driving me to appointments. I've lived my life, and they have so much ahead of them. It just feels like the more I linger, the more I'm actually stealing from their lives. Does that make sense?",
